==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monoclinic
<hw>Mon`o*clin"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mono-</ets> + Gr. <?/ to incline.]</ety>
<fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>Having one oblique intersection; -- said
of that system of crystallization in which the vertical axis is inclined
to one, but at right angles to the other, lateral axis. See
<er>Crystallization</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monoclinous</ent>⟦br⟧
